11/01/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The newly established Kosovo Security Force (KSF) will become operational on January 21st, media reported on Saturday (January 10th).
According to a senior KFOR official, the current Kosovo Protection Corps (KPC) is to be disbanded on January 20th, and the KSF will assume its duties a day later.
Observers expect President Fatmir Sejdiu to appoint at least six generals in charge of the KSF by January 20th.
NATO will monitor its training.
(Blic, Zeri, BTA - 10/01/09)
